==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Siderography
<hw>Sid`er*og"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/<?/<?/ iron + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or practice of
steel engraving; especially, the process, invented by Perkins, of
multiplying facsimiles of an engraved steel plate by first rolling over
it, when hardened, a soft steel cylinder, and then rolling the cylinder,
when hardened, over a soft steel plate, which thus becomes a facsimile
of the original. The process has been superseded by
<xex>electrotypy</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siderolite</ent>⟦br⟧
